📌 Summary

Algorithms are foolproof step-by-step recipes—not just for computers, but for life itself. Making fufu, haggling at markets, sending M-Pesa reversals—all follow precise sequences that anyone can replicate. We designed SMS-based crop price alerts for farmers with basic Nokia phones: clear logic where "TOMATO ADDIS" triggers a price reply without apps or internet. Key insight: test algorithms manually before coding—walk through each step with a friend. Design for constraints: compress messages ("T45↑7%"), support local languages, handle edge cases like sudden rain. The best algorithms feel invisible—they just work when needed. Remember: you're not learning to code. You're learning to codify wisdom so it scales beyond one village, one lifetime, one grandmother's memory.

 

